	<div class="posts">
	<a name="107990504897619666">&nbsp;</a><br>
	<a href="http://cyber.law.harvard.edu/icann/mdr2001/archive/pres/bellovin-keynote.html">ICANN and Internet Security</a>.&nbsp; This is Steven Bellovin's keynote address to the November 2001 ICANN meeting and workshop.  A key slide is the identification of the major components, and the difficulty of securing a total system (i.e., the Internet completely) with distributed responsibilities.<br>
	<span class="byline">posted by Dennis at <a href="#107990504897619666">Sunday, March 21, 2004</a></span></div>
